{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"compacted_at":1783785015146389002,"compiled_state":{"alias":"demoniac-cerebral-coral","assignee":"claude-opus","author":"RebarBotNava","bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-207_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"459f9aff-35f0-4598-b1eb-64245ff97c2f","comments":[{"author":"RebarBotNava","body":"Root cause + fix implemented on branch fix/optionality-failure-lazy-import.\n\nFIX (src/rebar/llm/failure.py): removed the module-scope `import httpx` and\n`from pydantic_ai.exceptions import (...)`. Those names are now imported LAZILY\ninside `_map()` and `_base_diagnostic()` (the two functions doing runtime\nisinstance checks), each guarded by `try/except ImportError` so classification\ndegrades to NEEDS_INVESTIGATION (non-retryable) — never ModuleNotFoundError —\nwhen the [agents] stack is absent (e.g. runner.preflight classifying a\nmissing-extra LLMConfigError). Annotations on the two private HTTP helpers relaxed\nto `Any` (module-scope heavy-type annotations, incl. under `if TYPE_CHECKING:`,\nare ALSO forbidden by the AST guard, which recurses into If bodies).\n\nAST-GUARD GAP (tests/unit/test_core_optionality.py): `_HEAVY` was a stale\nLangChain-era list (langchain/langgraph/anthropic/inspect_ai/opentelemetry/...).\nAdded `pydantic_ai` and `httpx` — the actual runtime heavy deps after the\npydantic-ai cutover (story d6d1). Verified RED-before / GREEN-after: with the\naddition, the guard flags exactly failure.py (sole offender) pre-fix and passes\npost-fix. failure.py is the ONLY module-scope offender in the core tree (all of\nrunner.py's pydantic_ai/httpx imports are already function-local).\n\nVERIFICATION so far (repo .venv, local build):\n- make lint: pass; make typecheck: pass (297 files).\n- tests/unit/test_core_optionality.py: 2 passed (guard now catches this class).\n- tests/unit/test_llm_failure_matrix.py: 35 passed (classification unchanged w/ extras).\n- Lean-path proof: with httpx+pydantic_ai import-blocked, `import rebar.llm.failure`\n  succeeds and classify -> NEEDS_INVESTIGATION (non-retryable), no raise.\n- optionality + llm-optionality subset: 51 passed, 11 skipped (clean-lane-only).\n- Full `make test`: running.","timestamp":1783784318664151001},{"author":"RebarBotNava","body":"DECISION — Gerrit Verified path (deliverable #4): the module-scope-heavy-import\nguard is ALREADY in the Verified path; the residual clean-wheel/packaging jobs are\njustified to stay post-merge.\n\nFindings:\n- gerrit-verify.yaml (the sole `Verified` voter) runs the SAME checks as test.yml\n  against the exact patchset, installing `.[dev]` -> `[agents]` (full heavy stack).\n- optionality.yml runs on `push`/`pull_request` only — i.e. GitHub branch/PR CI. It\n  casts NO Gerrit vote. Since code lands via Gerrit (not GitHub PRs), its\n  clean-core-wheel job only ran POST-merge on `main`, which is why the regression\n  reached `main` visibly-red instead of being blocked.\n- BUT: the static AST guard\n  `tests/unit/test_core_optionality.py::test_no_core_module_imports_heavy_stack_at_module_scope`\n  is a normal unit test collected by `pytest -m \"not integration and not external\"`\n  == `make test` == the gerrit-verify default suite. Confirmed it is selected under\n  that marker filter. So it DOES run in the Verified gate on every patchset.\n\nConsequence: fixing `_HEAVY` (this ticket) extends the Verified gate to block THIS\nregression class (module-scope heavy imports) pre-merge, deterministically and for\nfree — no workflow rewiring. This is the exact mechanism of the incident, so the gap\nis genuinely closed in the pre-merge gate.\n\nWhy NOT fold the full optionality workflow (clean-core-wheel + per-extra + union\njobs) into gerrit-verify:\n1. Disproportionate cost. Those jobs need a fundamentally different install matrix\n   (build wheel -> N fresh no-extras venvs -> per-extra installs -> union resolve).\n   They cannot reuse build-and-test's already-`[dev]` environment, so they'd be\n   several NEW parallel jobs on EVERY per-patchset Verified vote (and under FF-only\n   submit, re-run on every rebase). Verified latency is already the throughput\n   bottleneck for landing.\n2. The high-value, high-frequency failure mode (module-scope heavy import) is now\n   covered in-Verified by the cheap in-process AST test. The clean-wheel job's unique\n   residual coverage is (a) dynamic/transitive import leaks the AST can't see and\n   (b) packaging/extras-resolution regressions — both lower-frequency, and (b) is\n   better gated at release than per-change.\n3. The clean-wheel jobs still run on every push to main (post-merge) and on the\n   GitHub PR mirror, so the safety net remains — it is just not a submit-blocker.\n\nNet: partial add (the guard that matters, already wired) + justified deferral of the\nheavyweight packaging jobs. If the team prefers belt-and-suspenders, the follow-up\nwould be to extract optionality's jobs into a reusable workflow called from both\noptionality.yml and gerrit-verify.yaml — filed as a separate optionality ticket if desired.","timestamp":1783784340806309001}],"created_at":1783784016570391001,"deps":[],"description":"## Summary\n\nThe `optionality` GitHub Actions workflow fails on every push to `main` (job\n\"clean core wheel (no extras → heavy deps absent)\"). `src/rebar/llm/failure.py`\nimports `httpx` and `pydantic_ai.exceptions` at **module scope**, so importing\nthe module in a no-extras (core-only) install raises\n`ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'pydantic_ai'` — breaking the lean-runtime\noptionality contract (extras may only ADD deps; core must import with none).\n\nIt reached `main` because the Gerrit `Verified` gate (gerrit-verify.yaml) installs\n`.[dev]` -> `[agents]` (heavy stack present), so the module-scope import succeeds\nthere; and the static AST guard that SHOULD catch it\n(`tests/unit/test_core_optionality.py::test_no_core_module_imports_heavy_stack_at_module_scope`,\nwhich DOES run inside `make test` = the Verified suite) has a stale `_HEAVY` list\nfrom the LangChain era — it is missing `pydantic_ai` and `httpx`, the actual\nruntime heavy deps after the pydantic-ai cutover.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n\n1. Build the core wheel with no extras, install into a clean venv\n   (`python -m build --wheel && pip install dist/*.whl`).\n2. `python -c \"import rebar.llm.failure\"`.\n\n- Expected: import succeeds (core stays lean; heavy imports are lazy).\n- Actual: `ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'pydantic_ai'` at\n  `src/rebar/llm/failure.py:27`; optionality clean-core-wheel job reports\n  `8 failed, 11 passed`.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n- `failure.py` module-scope `import httpx` + `from pydantic_ai.exceptions import (...)`.\n- `_HEAVY` in `tests/unit/test_core_optionality.py` omits `pydantic_ai`/`httpx`,\n  so the in-Verified static guard never flagged the offender.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `src/rebar/llm/failure.py` performs NO module-scope import of `httpx` or\n      `pydantic_ai`; those imports are lazy (function-local), matching the\n      established pattern in `runner.py`. Type annotations remain valid under\n      `from __future__ import annotations`.\n- [ ] `classify_llm_failure(...)` still classifies correctly WITH the agents\n      extra present, and degrades safely (returns NEEDS_INVESTIGATION, never\n      raises ModuleNotFoundError) when the heavy stack is ABSENT.\n- [ ] `_HEAVY` in `tests/unit/test_core_optionality.py` includes `pydantic_ai`\n      and `httpx`, so the static module-scope guard catches this regression class.\n- [ ] The AST guard fails on the unfixed code (RED) and passes after the fix (GREEN).\n- [ ] The optionality workflow clean-core-wheel job passes (module imports under\n      a no-extras install).\n- [ ] Decision recorded on the Gerrit Verified path: the module-scope-heavy-import\n      guard is confirmed to run inside the Verified suite via the AST test; the\n      residual clean-wheel/packaging jobs are justified as post-merge (or wired in).\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass locally.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/llm/failure.py","reason":"lazy heavy imports (httpx/pydantic_ai) at call boundary"},{"path":"tests/unit/test_core_optionality.py","reason":"add pydantic_ai/httpx to _HEAVY AST-guard list"}],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[],"parent_id":null,"parent_status_uuid":"ca531f4f-8cb4-406c-ad7a-efc8d4908cc5","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"signature":null,"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"0582-74a2-1811-43f0","ticket_type":"bug","title":"optionality CI red on main: src/rebar/llm/failure.py imports pydantic_ai/httpx at module scope","verify_commands":[{"command":"make lint","dd_id":"DD1","dd_text":"lint+format clean"},{"command":"make typecheck","dd_id":"DD2","dd_text":"types clean"},{"command":"python -m pytest tests/unit/test_core_optionality.py tests/unit/test_llm_failure_matrix.py -q","dd_id":"DD3","dd_text":"AST guard + failure matrix pass"}]},"source_event_uuids":["70b34a0c-2216-4e41-9706-cde5f36125a2","ca531f4f-8cb4-406c-ad7a-efc8d4908cc5","2e964b8f-ef2e-44a3-8a73-ae53a11265a2","f3b11d2f-809e-4b45-8adf-34780f89edf1","80cac80b-ae99-4dd9-be3f-e927e3bc97db","a813cfff-6e20-4f38-bd9e-ae183f93c087","c47cc774-07e2-4c33-9521-f586ee092693"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1783785015146389002,"uuid":"84f25ca7-4693-49a3-9587-686ee95e16b7"}